TITLE: Dependency Injection Token Naming in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Defines a naming convention for dependency injection tokens using a constant with the same interface name, assigned by calling createIdentifier with a string formatted as '<package-name>.<service-or-controller-name>.(service|controller)'. This ensures consistent and recognizable tokens across the project.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dream-num/univer/blob/dev/docs/NAMING_CONVENTION.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
export const IYourServiceOrControllerName = createIdentifier<IYourServiceOrControllerName>('<package-name>.<your-service-or-controller-name>.(service|controller>');

// ‚úÖ
export const ILogService = createIdentifier<ILogService>('core.log.service');

// üö´
export const ILogService = createIdentifier<ILogService>('log-service');
```

