TITLE: Interface Naming Convention in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Specifies that all interfaces should be named with a capital 'I' prefix, which aids in recognizing interfaces easily within the codebase. Demonstrates with accepted and rejected naming examples.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dream-num/univer/blob/dev/docs/NAMING_CONVENTION.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// ‚úÖ
export interface IMyInterface {}

// üö´
export interface MyInterface {}
```

