TITLE: Plugin Class Naming Convention in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Mandates that plugin classes should be named with PascalCase and prefixed by 'Univer' to indicate their origin and role clearly within the framework. Examples clarify the difference between compliant and non-compliant naming.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dream-num/univer/blob/dev/docs/NAMING_CONVENTION.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// ‚úÖ
export class UniverFilterPlugin extends Plugin {}

// üö´
export class FilterPlugin extends Plugin {}
```

